  "text": "The Kubernetes API server admission webhook chain is implemented across several key components in the apiserver staging directory:\n\n**Core Framework (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/)**:\n- `chain.go` implements chainAdmissionHandler which orchestrates multiple admission handlers through Admit() and Validate() methods\n- `interfaces.go` defines the core admission interfaces: Interface, MutationInterface, and ValidationInterface\n\n**Webhook Admission Controller**:\n- `plugin/webhook/mutating/plugin.go` - Implements the MutatingAdmissionWebhook plugin that registers as an admission plugin and delegates to the generic webhook\n- `plugin/webhook/validating/plugin.go` - Implements the ValidatingAdmissionWebhook plugin similarly\n- Both use Register() functions to register with the admission plugins registry\n\n**Generic Webhook Base**:\n- `plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go` - The Webhook struct serves as the base implementation for both mutating and validating webhooks. It implements the Dispatch() method which:\n  1. Calls ShouldCallHook() to determine which webhooks should be invoked based on namespace selectors, object selectors, rules, and match conditions\n  2. Delegates to the specific Dispatcher (mutating or validating) for webhook invocation\n- `plugin/webhook/generic/interfaces.go` - Defines the Dispatcher interface that mutating and validating dispatchers implement\n\n**Webhook Call Dispatch**:\n- `plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go` - Implements mutatingDispatcher which sequentially calls each mutating webhook and applies JSON patches to the object. Key method: Dispatch() calls callAttrMutatingHook() for each webhook\n- `plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go` - Implements validatingDispatcher which calls validating webhooks in parallel using goroutines and aggregates errors. Key method: Dispatch() spawns goroutines and collects results via error channel\n\n**Admission Response Aggregation**:\n- `plugin/webhook/request/admissionreview.go` - Handles creation of AdmissionReview objects and verification of webhook responses through CreateAdmissionObjects() and VerifyAdmissionResponse(). The latter extracts audit annotations, allowed decision, patches, and warnings\n- `plugin/webhook/mutating/reinvocationcontext.go` - Manages reinvocation of webhooks when mutations occur\n\n**Webhook Accessors and Matching**:\n- `plugin/webhook/accessors.go` - WebhookAccessor interface provides unified access to both mutating and validating webhook configurations\n- `plugin/webhook/predicates/namespace/matcher.go` - Matches webhooks against namespace selectors\n- `plugin/webhook/predicates/object/matcher.go` - Matches webhooks against object selectors  \n- `plugin/webhook/predicates/rules/rules.go` - Matches webhooks against API group, version, resource, and operation rules\n- `plugin/webhook/matchconditions/matcher.go` - Evaluates CEL match conditions on webhooks\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- `util/webhook/error.go` - Defines ErrCallingWebhook for transport errors and ErrWebhookRejection for webhook rejections\n- Dispatchers differentiate between these error types to implement fail-open and fail-closed policies\n\nThe chain flows: API Server → chainAdmissionHandler.Admit/Validate() → MutatingAdmissionWebhook/ValidatingAdmissionWebhook plugins → Webhook.Dispatch() → mutatingDispatcher/validatingDispatcher.Dispatch() → individual webhook calls with response verification."
}

